      • isInCollection

        public static <T> boolean isInCollection(T ele,
                                         Collection<T> coll)
        Checks whether ele is in the given coll. Comparison is done by invoking Collection.contains(Object).
        Be careful of incorrect equals() implementation (e.g. not calling super.equals()) as this may lead to incorrect result.
        Type Parameters:
        T - type of element
        Parameters:
        ele - to be evaluated against
        coll - to be iterated over
        Returns:
        true if element is found in the collection.
        false if either of the following is true:
        • element is null
        • collection is empty or null
        • element is not found in the collection

        Type Parameters:
        E - type of enum
        Parameters:
        e - to be checked
        enums - to be iterated over
        Returns:
        true if e is found in enums.
        false if either of the following is true:

        • enums is null
        • e is not found in enums
